This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories, as it presents a new distributed caching mechanism for load balancing in large-scale storage systems. The paper also involves network flows and queuing theory, which are relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Performance (cs.PF) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use case for emerging switch-based caching, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
